ranslations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be asleep"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hide, to conceal (something)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be unaware, to be uncaring, to pay no consideration on; to neglect, to disregard, to omit carelessly and intentionally","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"[…] وَدَّ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا لَوْ تَغْفُلُونَ عَنْ أَسْلِحَتِكُمْ وَأَمْتِعَتِكُمْ فَيَمِيلُونَ عَلَيْكُمْ مَيْلَةً وَاحِدَةً […]","english":"Those who disbelieve wish that ye would neglect your weapons and your useful belongings so they could come down upon you in one encroachment."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to neglect, overlook, be or become oblivious to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to accuse of negligence or overlooking or obliviousness to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make [+direct object] overlook, neglect, be or become oblivious to"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32136","headword_ar":"غُفْلٌ","root":"gfl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Land"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without cultivation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without any way-mark:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without any waymark and without cultivation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not rained upon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unknown; in which is no known trace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vestige:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and, accord. to the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2276},{"kind":"text","text":"M,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waterless desert, that causes one to lose his way, wherein is no sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agofaAlN","text_ar":"اَغْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAtN","text_ar":"مَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S:) and Lh mentions the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN A^agofaAlN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ اَغْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though they made every portion thereof to be what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gufolN","text_ar":"غُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bilaAdN A^agofaAlN","text_ar":"بِلَادٌ اَغْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tracts of country"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wherein are no way-marks by which to be directed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also A road, or way, &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no sign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, whereby it may be known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And A gaming-arrow ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidoHN","text_ar":"قِدْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which is no mark"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notch to distinguish it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as has no portion assigned to it, and no fine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) [or,] accord. to Lh, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidaAHN gufolN","text_ar":"قِدَاحٌ غُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", using the sing. form [of the epithet] meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gaming arrows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are no notches, and to which is assigned no portion and no fine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"they used to be added to give additional weight to the collection of arrows from fear of occasioning suspicion [of foul play], i. e. to increase the number: and they were four; the first [called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuSad~aru","text_ar":"المُصَدَّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuDaE~afu","text_ar":"المُضَعَّفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaniyHu","text_ar":"المَنِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the next,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~afiyHu","text_ar":"السَّفِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  And A beast ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~apN","text_ar":"دَابَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no brand upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is not branded, in order that the poor-rate may not be"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considered as"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incumbent for her:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gufulN","text_ar":"غُفُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. thereof, or is used by poetic license: the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agofaAlN","text_ar":"اَغْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The pl. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agofaAlN","text_ar":"اَغْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is also applied to Camels, or cattle, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEamN","text_ar":"نَعَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that yield no milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSoHaf","text_ar":"مُصْحَف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or copy of the Kur-án]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bare of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"signs called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaA$ir","text_ar":"عَوَاشِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA$irapN","text_ar":"عَاشِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like of these."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And A book, or writing, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is anonymous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the author is not named."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And Poetry"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the author is unknown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And A poet"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unknown"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and unnamed"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anonymous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agofaAlN","text_ar":"اَغْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-  Also A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inexperienced in affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, TA.) One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose beneficence is not hoped for, nor his evilness feared;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he being like the shackled that is neglected:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (TA.) And One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of whom one knows not what he possesses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fur"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft portions of hair,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awobaAr","text_ar":"اَوْبَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", [perhaps because long left unshorn,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","S","O","Ks","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n32137","headword_ar":"غَفَلٌ","root":"gfl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gafolapN","text_ar":"غَفْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also [Such as is]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant and high"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in estimation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. of the means of subsistence]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyrN rafiyEN","text_ar":"كَثِيرٌ رَفِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K: [or the latter word is correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiygN","text_ar":"رَفِيغٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the TK,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample, and pleasant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to the means of subsistence:]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of ampleness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the means of subsistence: (O, K:) thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa fiY gafalK mino Eayo$ihi","text_ar":"هُوَ فِى غَفَلٍ مِنْ عَيْشِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in a state of ampleness in respect of his means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. thus termed as being a cause of unmindfulness, or heedlessness]. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n32138","headword_ar":"غُفُلٌ","root":"gfl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gufolN","text_ar":"غُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}